sections.comments: PREREQUISITE: MUSC 221 OR PERMISSION OF INSTRUCTOR.  If class is full, register for WAITLIST, as available. Unfortunately, due to high enrollment levels for MUSC 358 - History of Jazz, the School has decided to limit enrollment to BMUS, BA - Music majors/minors and music graduate students. For further information or to request special exemption from this rule, please contact the instructor of the course, Dr. Metzer at david.metzer@ubc.ca.
Wait list for MUSC 358 001. Students will be moved to the class in order of DATE REGISTRATION on this waitlist, as/if space becomes available in the class.

description: Jazz styles and their cultural contexts; the relationship of performers and audiences; issues of race and gender; non-Western influences.
